4. Jenkins Create Pipeline as code -  Short Trick

a. Run pipeline by pipeline script from SCM.
When you write Jenkins code this You can be store this code to GitHub for version control:
1. Create a new github repo
2. Copy Jenkins code and paste on new file
3. File name should be Jenkins file
4. From Jenkins: create new job
a. Select pipeline script from SCM
b. select git
c. Fill necessary details
d. Select branch as per GitHub repo
e. Run the job

To easy write the codes:
1. To write the code can be write on VScode with Jenkins plugin.
2. By using Pipeline Syntax which help you to write groovy code for pipeline



5. Jenkins Create Pipeline as code -   Easiest Way To Write Jenkinsfile (Blue Ocean)
Blue Ocean is a Jenkins plugin that provides a modern, visual, and user-friendly interface to create, view, and manage Jenkins pipelines easily.

1. Go to plugin and install Blue Ocean
2. back to Jenkins default dashboard and click on Blue Ocean
a. where can run pipeline
b. restart any stages
c. Create new pipeline from GitHub repo
